<br>
I think along the lines of scenario 2. Though doing the right thing is inherently rewarding, we don't do it in order to &quot;gain a reward&quot;. Like, you find showing your parents the respect they deserve satisfying, even though that isn't the reason you do it necesarily.  Are we very far off from each other in our thinking there?<br>
